</m:mtd>
</m:mtr>
</m:mtable>
</m:math>
</para>
<para id="element-38">
A situation, where measurement of force is required, assumes that mass is invariant. We proceed to measure force either in terms of acceleration or change in momentum in equivalent manner. 
</para>
<section id="section-1a">
<title> Force as product of mass and acceleration </title>
<example id="example-39">
<para id="element-39"><term>Problem : </term> A bullet of 10 gram enters into a wooden target with a speed of 200 m/s and comes to stop with constant deceleration. If linear penetration into the wood is 10 cm, then find the force on the bullet.
</para>
