</para>
<para id="element-17">The additional term, therefore, is not an “effect” term like “ma”, but a "cause" term representing “external force”, which results from the exchange of mass with the surrounding. 
</para>
<para id="element-17a">Clearly, there is no other external force other than thrust that gives such a great acceleration to a rocket. Gravitational and air resistance actually retards the motion of a rocket moving vertically upward. Thus, we can safely say that thrust is the only force that imparts acceleration in the direction of the motion of the rocket. In case rocket is fired from a region where other external forces like that of gravity and air resistance can be neglected, then we can put , F = 0. Then,</para>
<para id="element-18">
<m:math display="block">
