<para id="element-31">
Yet another important aspect of force here is that force and acceleration vectors need not be parallel or in the same direction.
</para>
<para id="element-32">
We summarize the discussion held, in the context of relativistic mechanics, so far as : 
</para>
<para id="element-33">
<list id="list-33" list-type="enumerated">
<item> Given mass is not invariant.
 </item>
<item> The momentum and acceleration forms of Newton’s second law are not equivalent.
 </item>
<item> Momentum form of Newton’s second law is valid.
 </item>
<item> Acceleration form of Newton’s second law is not valid.
 </item>
<item> Force and acceleration need not be in the same direction.
 </item>
</list>
</para>
